caption: This is the best place in Chicago.
Great food and drinks.
Kite String had their patio open on an unexpectedly warm day. The bartenders were as cool as always and very knowledgeable about the Chicago craft brewing scene!

Who in their right mind would give this place 1 star? Vegetarian options to every meat filled taquito! the whole $20menu can be tailored to your preferences! The cocktails are all on point! I would personally love more cider selections but hey pour me another cocktail and i’ll be fine! The staff is great! Every time i’ve been in it’s been wonderful!
Great Beer and drink selection. Great atmosphere. Favorite spot for a beer on a nice day

A great corner bar/restaurant before and during Covid-19! Clean, spacious, airy, and following all guidelines.  You can still get the delicious house made taquitos and other tasty sundries to take home. Grab a bubbler cocktail or tasty draft to sip there AND take some with you in their stylish to-go containers. Awesome owners and fun staff especially Mary Mac who always make you feel welcomed and taken care of.
Cool little bar.
Good place.
We look forward to Fridays to say hi to the nice folks at Kite String and find out what surprises they have in store for us!
(Translated by Google) the taquitos!  (Original) the taquitos!
Cool vibes, great drinks, awesome people!
Great place with great service! We come here a lot! Really awesome mezcal selection and be sure to check out the secret menu for special taquitos.
It’s fun and the prices are great, not the biggest fan of the taquitos, maybe I’m just picky? Great staff and drinks
Spent NYE 2019 here. Cute cozy. Fabulous duck wings.
Fantastic taquitos!

Mostly a local hangout, despite being next to a CTA station. The staff is fantastic, always friendly. The taquitos are amazing, but the Wednesday ribs are worth the trip. As a bonus, they have a rotating tap of local brews and spirits.

Stopped in hear on a whim while back in town and was not disappointed. The barkeep was incredibly polite and chill. The food was incredibly reasonably priced and astoundingly delicious. The tomatillo avocado salsa was to die for, literally I'd die for it. Pairing your more standard tortilla chips with beet chips was also an ingenious move, I might just acquired a new addiction.  Their taquitos are where Kite String really shines: savory and succulent. They are basically the perfect drunk food and I regret that I wasn't drunk when I had them to confirm this suspicion. Be sure to stop in here for some great cocktails, food, and company.
Limited menu and not all of it is great. But none of it is bad thus far. Friendly staff and laid back place.

Cool place. Small menu that focuses on Taquitos, and done pretty well. Everything is made in house, including shells, sauces and special spice blend. Prices weren't bad for the quality of food you're getting. We found them to be a bit salty but otherwise great. At the back of the bar in the cubby with books and what not there is a specials board, don't forget to check it out.
Great drinks and great ribs!
"Takitos" were same as frozen microwave bites and drink was flat and tasted like water

I've been here a few times recently and have come away happy, taken care of and more than a little buzzed on each occasion!  I've only been right around opening, but my bartender, Mary Mac, crushes it on hospitality. Funny, real and attentive, she's another in long line of top-notch Chicago barkeeps. The fact that her lovely husband, Virgil, is typically perched at the other end of the bar adds to the homey, neighborhood vibe that I love.  The taquitos are yummy and weird, the bubbler drinks flavorful and potent, and the specials are solid deals. It's hard not to like this spot.
Cute place!! Friendly staff.
Great staff amazing music dope vibes
Go here on Wednesdays and get you a room dinner. CRAZY GOOD! The menu is tasty and cheap. The place has a real laid back ambiance.

This place is quirky and awesome. Love taquitos ? They've got amazing ones and veggie chips with salsa. And cocktails on tap and draft beer. And a vibe you can't find elsewhere. Worth a visit. Or three. Or a million.
Great drinks and little tacos!

Great rib special on wednesdays. $20 for a half rack, salad, chips/guac, and a little chocolate dessert. Gotta come back for the taquitos. Seems like they're a solid cheap eat at $2 a pop. Staff is very friendly, and an overall chill vibe. Definitely would recommend

All food is made from scratch and you can eat as long as the bar's open. Love the homemade tortillas which they use for the chips as well. Their vegetarian taquito is always tasty (usually a beet tortilla). Bubbler drinks are genius, and delicious to boot.
Wonderful vibe, wonderful owners. High recommend.
Great beer selection and tasty taquitos
Great food and drinks, keep an eye out for the secret menu while you are there.
Amazing cocktails and the best taquitos I've ever had!

Want to love this place. The design and concept are really great. Food is tasty and interesting -- perfect evalated bar food.  Staff are polite, but could use some service training. Multiple times, different staff, even when it's practically deserted, it can be hard to get the bartender's attention, even while standing at the bar. Even when they're not busy, the bartender doesn't bring over drinks or food -- you'll have to get up to get it.  Most recent visit, with only five people there, I stood three minutes to order a beer, waited five at my table while it was being poured (though maybe keg had to be changed or something), then another two standing at the bar to have it taken from the tap and handed to me.  The Pacman machine needs quarters, but they only had a couple dollars' worth in the register.  Ultimately, all this leads to smaller check sizes.  It's good. Just so frustrating to see it fall short of great.

Excellent cocktails from a creative bartender, Damian. Test him on a Momday night. The vibe is totally chill and comfortable. The menu looks incredible: taquitos, beet chips and dips. Next time I'm coming hungry. You should too!
Fun bar. Cold beers. Good service. Chill vibes.  I'm new to the area and I will definitely be returning
A pleasant find in the neighborhood! Good selection of beers, excellent taquitos and friendly staff. 5/5 will visit again!

If I go to long without going to Kite String I start going through withdrawl.  This is a place you can hop off the brown line spontaneously after work, hang out and always feel at home.  And I do!  The Bubblers are awesome.  The homemade chips and creative dips are delicious.  This is the only place I've been able to find vegan taquitos.  Thank you!
Staff is really nice, food is fun, delicious and affordable, cool place to hang out. Highly recommended.
Delicious taquitos
Good drink options

I have driven by a number of times and wanted to stop in, finally did yesterday. It's immediately off the brown line (Addison) which is ideal. The menu is incredibly inexpensive and everything that I tried (3 out of 4 taquitos), Hurricane bubbler, a draft beer, was outstanding. Really nice owner working the bar. It's absolutely one of my favorite spots on the north side.
Great beers and creative $2 taquitos

The owner (who acts as bartender) was so friendly and the food was fresh and delicious! Everything but the dessert was made in-house, and even that was made just down the street. We were unfortunately unable to try the drinks, but they appeared to be varied and diverse. The menu changes with the seasons, so you'll never find the same thing twice. The entire menu was just a little over $20, and that was only because I got a soda that was produced in Wisconsin. It was enough for 2 people. It's located right down the street from the Addison CTA station, and tucked away on a cozy corner.

Delicious! We got everything on the menu and it was all really good. The place itself is really well done. Comfortable. And the service was as good as everyone says. This is going to be our new local!
Great local spot. Good pre made cocktails and tasty bar snacks
Great local place near addison brown line.
Amazing menu, great drinks and a great social space. Highly recommend
It has noms. It has gulps. And they are both tasty!

Awesome neighbor bar! Everything we ordered was delicious, both drinks and food. We had the chips with the tomatillo avocado dip. Awesome! One each of the taquitos. All four were awesome! For drinks, we got the Mango Mule bubbler and Hibiscus Negroni bubbler. Both, you guessed it, awesome!
Good drinks...we got the app sampler and it was plenty for 2 to 3 people.
My fav bar with the best drinks and little snacks in the whole neighborhood
Damn, taquitos are delicious!
Great casual place for cheap snacks and unique twists on cocktails
Great small bar. Perfect for snacks
Nice corner bar
Such a good spot! Craft beers on tap (15+) and taquitos & chips that satisfy. Come on over!

SO HAPPY we found this spot during our trip to Chicago! Absolutely incredible, friendly service. Great drinks, great insight on local flavors, breweries and drinks - and you just can't beat Ms. Pacman! Also loved that they serve food 24/7 - WONDERFUL in-house taquitos, beet chips and salsa! Love Kite String Cantina!

Their only entree is a variety of taquitos (veggie option available) but damn are they tasty. Very friendly week night staff and cozy atmosphere, there is Ms. PAC-Man so obviously a win. Honestly this place is a quick late night hero, unfortunately I don’t drink but they seemed to have a very large selection of fruity cocktails and beers on tap. I also spotted a $5 happy hour, all said and done this place makes a great first impression.
Love this place! The bubbler cocktails are fun, and the menu is small and affordable. Love that you can try the whole menu for $20. 🙂 Great spot to hang out with some friends for a bit.
Cute place. Great cocktails and taquitos.
Waitress was rude! Drinks were good.

I wanted to go in here Sunday night. I was confused as to of if they were open or not. The lights were up so bright it looked like it was last call but it was 11pm the doors were open and plenty of people were sitting at the bar. I’ll come back another night the space looked like it would be cool and worth checking out.
Cool little place, taquitos are simple but delicious, good beers.
Awesome draft beer selection and the most delicious horchata cocktails North of the border. The bartender is awesome and the taquitos really hit the spot!

WOW! My new favorite bar in the entire city!! The food and cocktails are AMAZING!! And cheap! Wonderful atmosphere, great music, Mrs Pacman, very cool movies and offbeat TV shows on the screens. It's basically your new favorite meet-up place. Highly recommend. Wish I lived closer!
Nice staff great neighborhood vibe

Super cute inside, very limited menu. Taquitos were just okay, we tried them all. I would probably just stick with the chicken. The pork and the potato ones were just okay. The veggie one was terrible. I did love the orange tortilla used to make the pork taquito, that was excellent. Beet chips were good but there was only 3 in our chip bowl. We only got one dip and it was just okay (the green one with avocado)  Beer selection was decent. Their pre-made drinks were not so good.  Overall I would say okay, probably recommend as a pre-party venture or late night snack when you are drunk coming home.
Best place in the neighborhood. Amazing service, delicious food and lots of drink options.

I was sorry to see Bangers & Lace go, but Kite String is ultimately better. The bubbler cocktails and beer list is on point and the taquitos, chips and choice of 3 dips are awesome and all super affordable. I highly recommend getting the whole menu for $20. Also the staff is super friendly and amazing, I think it's a husband and wife duo.
my favorite bar
My husband, friends and I had a great time at happy hour here! Such good food and drinks, and extremely reasonably priced. Love the taquitos! Thanks for a great kickstart to the weekend
Great local bar! Good selection of draft beers, fun cocktails, and an awesome 80s playlist.
True neighborhood gem! Great vibe, my favorite food (homemade taquitos), and awesome bubbler cocktails! Also Ms. Pac Man.
Comfortable spot to stop in for a few.  Friendly staff,  good drink options.  Recommended!
This place is awesome! Great taquitos, drinks, and atmosphere at a homey neighborhood spot.
